profiles.name: Genetic Ancestry
profiles.description: Genetic ancestries were determined using five different methods as described in Carrot-Zhang et al (2020). These consensus calls were created based on the ancestral population that received the majority of assignments for each patient. The original data is here.

profiles.name: Putative copy-number alterations from GISTIC
profiles.description: Putative copy-number from GISTIC 2.0. Values: -2 = homozygous deletion; -1 = hemizygous deletion; 0 = neutral / no change; 1 = gain; 2 = high level amplification.

profiles.name: Log2 copy-number values
profiles.description: Log2 copy-number values for each gene (from Affymetrix SNP6).

profiles.name: Methylation (HM27 and HM450 merge)
profiles.description: Methylation between-platform (hm27 and hm450) normalization values.

profiles.name: Mutations
profiles.description: Mutation data from whole exome sequencing of 585 Ovarian Serous Cystadenocarcinoma samples.

profiles.name: Phosphoprotein site level expression data by CPTAC (TMT, Log2ratio)
profiles.description: Phosphoprotein site level expression data given in log-ratio (normalized) by CPTAC.

profiles.name: Protein levels (mass spectrometry by CPTAC)
profiles.description: Protein levels measured with mass spectrometry by the Clinical Proteomic Tumor Analysis Consortium (CPTAC)

profiles.name: Protein level z-scores (mass spectrometry by CPTAC)
profiles.description: Protein level z-scores measured with mass spectrometry by the Clinical Proteomic Tumor Analysis Consortium (CPTAC)
